    "In developing our toolkit, as shown in Figure 1, we categorize existing and anticipated model merging techniques.",
    "This classification enhances understanding by focusing on two critical aspects: weight initializations and the architectural configurations of various checkpoints.",
    "This section explores model merging techniques using LMC (Nagarajan and Kolter, 2019) to derive a final merged model through linear interpolation.",
    "A key requirement is that the models must have identical architectures and initializations.",
    "The simplest method, built upon the results of weight averaging literature (Utans, 1996; Smith and Gashler, 2017; Garipov et al., 2018; Izmailov et al., 2018) and the Model Soups (Wortsman et al., 2022) approach, is linear averaging of weights."
